Air elementals resemble amorphous, shifting clouds surrounded by fast-moving currents of air. Darker bits of twirling vapor resemble eyes and mouths.
Their language, Auran, sounds like the high-pitched shriek of a tornado or the low moan of a midnight storm. Their queen is Akadi. 

